        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 11:04PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1104 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Chupadera Ranch Airport, or 26 miles south of Carrizo
Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Webb
County.

This includes US Highway 83 near mile marker 668.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
